 NEW LIBRARY IN NORA.     DESCRIBES NORA'S NEW PUBLIC LIBRARY OPENED IN JAN 81. NORA HAS 10,000INHABITANTS AND IS WITHIN COMMUTING DISTANCE OF OREBRO. THE LIBRARY WAS BUILTIN THE TOWN CENTRE AND THE EXTERIOR FITS IN WELL WITH THE OLD SURROUNDINGS. ITOCCUPIES 1000 SQ.M. BUILDING SHARED WITH 2 BUSINESS COMPANIES. ALL PUBLICAREAS ARE PLACED ON THE GROUND FLOOR WITH DIRECT ACCESS FROM OUTSIDE. THELIBRARY GIVES ACCESS TO AN ASSEMBLY HALL AND A MEETING ROOM, THE LATTER PLACEDSO THAT IT BREAKS UP THE OTHERWISE LARGE LIBRARY HALL. DESCRIBES THE INTERIORDECORATION, INCLUDING THE BIRCH WOOD SHELVING AND FURNITURE, LIGHTING AND WALLTAPESTRY BY A LOCAL ARTIST